Mr Lutendo Ramahala (28) of Vhumatshelo Crop Farming at Tshikhwani was recognised as the best young farmer during the National Youth in Agriculture Fisheries and Forestry&nbsp;competition held at the Kieviets Kroon Country Estate in Pretoria last Friday.Ramahala won the smallholder category and received R50 000 and a certificate.During the event, the Deputy Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries,&nbsp;Bheki Cele, said that his department wanted&nbsp;to assist young people, particularly those from previously disadvantaged rural areas, in their farming endeavours.According to him, emerging farmers are playing an important role in food production. He encouraged&nbsp;young people to become involved by starting gardens at the back of their houses. &quot;We appreciate and value the contribution of young people in economic activities of the province,&quot; said Cele.Ramahala farms with spinach and tomatoes and sells these to a big supermarket and to members of the community. He currently employs five people.